This paper deals with the automatic diagnosis of retinal diseases using a hybrid model of support vector machine (SVM) and deep neural networks (DNNs). The paper proposes a new clinical retina dataset, EyeNet2, which incorporates 52 retina disease classes. The paper uses machine learning techniques to achieve high accuracy in diagnosis, which suggests that it belongs to the computer vision (cs.CV), machine learning (cs.LG), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with medical imaging and diagnosis, which suggests that it could also belong to the medical informatics (cs.MED) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories.
